<span id="freeTextContainer16760946983246392211">I have been in the habit lately of using gifs in my reviews, so it is likely that you will see some here.<br/><br/>Oh, wait! I feel one coming on - this was me this entire book:<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1405976866ra/10480539.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Holy cow! This book was a rush! I thought things were intense and suspenseful in previous Preston and Child books, but they raised the bar and way outdid themselves. I have no clue how they fit so much action, mystery, suspense and general bad-ass-ery into one book. <br/><br/>Here is a quick summary in gifs:<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504831307ra/23829581.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504831307ra/23829579.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504831466ra/23829623.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1504831624ra/23829663.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Finally - if only Antonio Banderas</span>
